description: An extremely large, reactor-powered passenger ferry that seats over a dozen.  Designed for medium range travel given the lack of cabins, but is often retrofitted for longer hauls. A spacer superstition dictates that passengers are to tip two yuan to a Charon pilot after a successful journey.
